---
alwaysApply: true
---

For backend Python code:
- Keep FastAPI routes thin.
- Put business logic in services.
- Put persistence logic in repositories/data access layers.
- Use Pydantic models for request/response boundaries.
- Use background jobs/queues for long-running tasks.
- Make side effects explicit.
- Prefer composable pure functions for data transformations.
- Add tests for core business logic, not just routes.
